The paper discusses the use of Multi-Armed Bandit (MAB) learning algorithms in IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also evaluates the performance of two classical MAB learning algorithms, UCB1 and Thompson Sampling, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Spectrum Access, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of intelligent devices, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
